==English==
===Etymology===
A combination of the surname of its inventor Adolphe Sax (1814-1894) + an O to make the word pronounceable + the English affix "[[phone]]", from Greek [[φωνή]], "voice".

===Noun===
'''saxaphone''' ([[saxophones]])

#A [[single reed instrument]] musical instrument of the [[woodwind]] family, usually made of [[brass]] and with a distinctive loop bringing the bell upwards

